======================================================================
PART 2: B_m(x) AS A GENERATING FUNCTION
======================================================================

prod(a + Q_k) = a^m B_m(1/a)
Setting x = 1/a: prod(1/x + Q_k) = (1/x)^m B_m(x)
So B_m(x) = x^m prod(Q_k + 1/x)

The ZEROS of B_m(x) are at x_k = -1/Q_k!
Since all Q_k > 0, all zeros of B_m are REAL and NEGATIVE.

