======================================================================
PART 3: PROD(a+Q_k) = a^m B_m(1/a) — THE FULL PICTURE
======================================================================

This gives us a PARAMETERIZED FAMILY of identities:

p=7, m=3:
  a=1: prod(1+Q) = F_{2m+1} = F_7 = 13
  d/da prod(a+Q)|_{a=1} = 20.0000
  = m·F_p - B'_m(1) = 3·13 - 19 = 20
  F_p · sum 1/(1+Q_k) = 13 · 1.538462 = 20.0000
  sum 1/(1+Q_k) = 1.538462
  = m - B'_m(1)/F_p = 3 - 1.461538
  B'_m(1)/F_p = 1.461538
  log-deriv B'_m(1)/B_m(1) = 1.461538

p=11, m=5:
  a=1: prod(1+Q) = F_{2m+1} = F_11 = 89
  d/da prod(a+Q)|_{a=1} = 235.0000
  = m·F_p - B'_m(1) = 5·89 - 210 = 235
  F_p · sum 1/(1+Q_k) = 89 · 2.640449 = 235.0000
  sum 1/(1+Q_k) = 2.640449
  = m - B'_m(1)/F_p = 5 - 2.359551
  B'_m(1)/F_p = 2.359551
  log-deriv B'_m(1)/B_m(1) = 2.359551

p=13, m=6:
  a=1: prod(1+Q) = F_{2m+1} = F_13 = 233
  d/da prod(a+Q)|_{a=1} = 744.0000
  = m·F_p - B'_m(1) = 6·233 - 654 = 744
  F_p · sum 1/(1+Q_k) = 233 · 3.193133 = 744.0000
  sum 1/(1+Q_k) = 3.193133
  = m - B'_m(1)/F_p = 6 - 2.806867
  B'_m(1)/F_p = 2.806867
  log-deriv B'_m(1)/B_m(1) = 2.806867

======================================================================
PART 4: FIBONACCI WORD AND TOURNAMENT MORPHISM
======================================================================

The Fibonacci word is the infinite binary word obtained from
the substitution S: 0→01, 1→0.
It encodes the 1D quasicrystal (Fibonacci chain).

Connection: the Interval tournament has generating set
S = {1,...,m} = the 'interval' in Z_p. The complement is
{m+1,...,p-1}. This partition of Z_p* into two halves
is the simplest possible — analogous to the Fibonacci
word's partition into 0s and 1s.

  F-word 2: 0000... (length 4)
  F-word 3: 00000000... (length 8)
  F-word 4: 0000000000000000... (length 16)
  F-word 5: 00000000000000000000000000000000... (length 32)
  F-word 6: 00000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000... (length 64)
  F-word 7: 00000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000... (length 128)

Key analogy:
  Fibonacci chain: 01001010010010100101...
  has diffraction peaks at positions n/φ mod 1

  Interval tournament: eigenvalues Q_k peak at k=1
  with Q_1/Q_2 → ∞ as p → ∞

  Both exhibit 'quasicrystalline order':
  - Not periodic (the Q_k are all different)
  - Not random (they follow a precise Chebyshev formula)
  - Self-similar (Morgan-Voyce recurrence = self-similar structure)

