  because F_p ≈ φ^p/√5 and p = 2m+1, so
  F_p^(1/m) ≈ (φ^(2m+1)/√5)^(1/m) → φ^2 = 2.618034

======================================================================
PART 7: FIBONACCI DIVISIBILITY LATTICE
======================================================================

Key property: F_m | F_n iff m | n.
So F_p is always coprime to F_q for distinct primes p, q > 5.

The Pisano period π(p) = period of F_n mod p:

  p= 5: π(p) =   20, F_p mod p = 0, (5/p) = +0
    p divides F_{p-(p+1)} = F_6
  p= 7: π(p) =   16, F_p mod p = 6, (5/p) = -1
    p divides F_{p-(p+1)} = F_8
  p=11: π(p) =   10, F_p mod p = 1, (5/p) = +1
    p divides F_{p-1} = F_10
  p=13: π(p) =   28, F_p mod p = 12, (5/p) = -1
    p divides F_{p-(p+1)} = F_14
  p=17: π(p) =   36, F_p mod p = 16, (5/p) = -1
    p divides F_{p-(p+1)} = F_18
  p=19: π(p) =   18, F_p mod p = 1, (5/p) = +1
    p divides F_{p-1} = F_18
  p=23: π(p) =   48, F_p mod p = 22, (5/p) = -1
    p divides F_{p-(p+1)} = F_24
  p=29: π(p) =   14, F_p mod p = 1, (5/p) = +1
    p divides F_{p-1} = F_28
  p=31: π(p) =   30, F_p mod p = 1, (5/p) = +1
    p divides F_{p-1} = F_30
  p=37: π(p) =   76, F_p mod p = 36, (5/p) = -1
    p divides F_{p-(p+1)} = F_38
  p=41: π(p) =   40, F_p mod p = 1, (5/p) = +1
    p divides F_{p-1} = F_40
  p=43: π(p) =   88, F_p mod p = 42, (5/p) = -1
    p divides F_{p-(p+1)} = F_44

  F_p ≡ (5/p) mod p (by Fibonacci reciprocity law)
  So prod(1+Q_k) ≡ (5/p) mod p

  This constrains the Q-spectrum modularly!

======================================================================
PART 8: FIBONACCI-TOURNAMENT DICTIONARY
======================================================================

| Fibonacci/Golden Ratio     | Tournament                          |
|----------------------------|-------------------------------------|
| F_p = prod(1+Q_k)          | Eigenvalue product of Interval      |
| φ² = lim F_p^{1/m}         | Geometric mean of 1+Q_k             |
| B_m(x) = Morgan-Voyce      | Generating function of e_j           |
| [[3,-1],[1,0]]^m           | Transfer matrix of ladder network   |
| Zeckendorf representation  | (Open) Decomposition of H?          |
| F_m | F_n iff m | n        | (Open) Divisibility in H?           |
| Pisano period π(p)         | Periodicity of F_p mod p            |
| Fibonacci word (quasicryst)| Dirichlet kernel (aperiodic order)  |
| φ = (1+√5)/2               | Eigenvalue of transfer matrix       |
| F_{p-1} + F_{p+1} = L_p    | Lucas = trace of T^m                |
| 1/φ + 1/φ² = 1             | Eigenvalue reciprocal sum = 1       |
| F_n² + F_{n+1}² = F_{2n+1} | Parseval-type identity for Q_k?     |

DEEPEST CONNECTION:
  The Interval tournament IS a 1D Fibonacci quasicrystal
  in frequency space. Its eigenvalues (Q_k) are the
  'phonon frequencies' of the Fibonacci chain. The identity
  prod(1+Q_k) = F_p says: the thermal partition function
  of this quasicrystal at temperature T = 1/ln(2) equals
  the p-th Fibonacci number.

UNEXPLORED DIRECTIONS:
  1. Does the Fibonacci LATTICE (2D, Penrose tiling)
     have an analogue for 2D tournaments?
  2. The golden ratio appears in KAM theory (stability
     of Hamiltonian systems). Does tournament stability
     (under perturbation of S) follow golden-ratio scaling?
  3. Fibonacci numbers count tilings of 1×n rectangles.
     Does F_p count tilings related to the tournament?
  4. The Binet formula F_p = (φ^p - ψ^p)/√5 means
     prod(1+Q_k) splits into TWO Galois-conjugate parts.
     This might connect to the Galois structure of Q(cos 2π/p).

